I’ve got the trace now. The live failure is a stale/misleading launcher lease plus missing IPC socket: the launcher sees `.mk-skill-advisor-launcher.json`, tries to bridge to the existing holder, finds no `daemon-ipc.sock`, writes `LEASE_HELD_BY... (no-bridge-socket)` to stdout, and the MCP client treats that as a failed native probe.
